By Esther Egbe
Super Eagles defender Kenneth Omeruo has penned a year loan deal with Leganes a team that is playing in the Top flight foorball in the Spanish League,National Daily learnt.
This is quite Huge for me I will play in the Spanish League and contribute my own quota to the Growth of the team Omeruo explained.
Amidst several offers we decided to settle down for Leganes because their offer suits my parent club Chelsea.I want to thank everyone who made this a reality.
A new beggining in a new club with great sense of focus for m e to achieve something great this season.
I have started work already because am now in spain looking forward to the first match of the season.The rock solid defender concluded.
